      <methods>
         <methodStep>
            <description>
               <section>
                  <title>Experimental Design</title>
                  <para>Probe readings are taken at 20 locations adjacent to vegetation monitoring plots.  The polts encompass a 30 m X 40 m area and are spaced 10m apart.
</para>
               </section>
               <section>
                  <title>Methods</title>
                  <para>Thaw depth is measured in centimeters using a metal probe at each of 20 vegetation plots at SL1A and SL1B. The probe point is 1.5m from the vegetation stake in line with the vegetation stake and the diagonal corner of the 1X1m veg plot. Measurements are done in mid to late September as close as possible to maximum thaw depth.
</para>
               </section>
            </description>
         </methodStep>
         <sampling>
            <studyExtent>
               <coverage>
                  <geographicCoverage>
                     <geographicDescription>SL1A -- In the summer of 2001 the Survey line fire burned a section of the Tanana flats just south of BCEF. This site was set up to match the rest of the floodplain successional sites except that instead of flooding the disturbance is fire. Before this site was burned it was and open black spruce forest with a feathermoss dominated ground cover.. Site alternate names: SL1B, BCEFY2</geographicDescription>
                     <boundingCoordinates>
